usage: smart_publish [-h] [--bump {none,patch,minor,major}]
                     [--version VERSION] [--pypirc PYPIRC] [--test]
                     [--skip-existing] [--no-build] [--no-upload]
                     [--repository REPOSITORY]
                     [--repository-url REPOSITORY_URL]
                     [--search-path SEARCH_PATH] [--dry-run]
                     [--platform {win32,win-amd64,linux-x86_64,linux-aarch64,macosx-x86_64,macosx-arm64,all}]
                     package

Smart package version manager and publisher

positional arguments:
  package               Name of the package to publish

options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --bump {none,patch,minor,major}
                        Version increment type (default: none)
  --version VERSION     Set specific version instead of auto-incrementing
  --pypirc PYPIRC       Path to custom .pypirc file
  --test                Use TestPyPI instead of PyPI
  --skip-existing       Skip existing versions on PyPI
  --no-build            Skip building distributions
  --no-upload           Skip uploading (build only)
  --repository REPOSITORY
                        Named repository from .pypirc
  --repository-url REPOSITORY_URL
                        Custom repository URL
  --search-path SEARCH_PATH
                        Additional directory to search for packages (can
                        repeat)
  --dry-run             Show version changes without publishing
  --platform {win32,win-amd64,linux-x86_64,linux-aarch64,macosx-x86_64,macosx-arm64,all}
                        Target platform(s) to build wheels for (can specify
                        multiple times or 'all')
